# Reliquary (yadm) repo-local ignores. The yadm work tree is $HOME, so git reads
# this file only for the yadm repo — nested project repos under $HOME are
# unaffected. Machine-wide OS/tool cruft lives in ~/.config/git/ignore (the XDG
# global excludes); project-specific rules like this one belong here instead.

# Homebrew Bundle lockfiles: deliberately NOT tracked. Homebrew is rolling-release,
# so the pinned bottle SHAs expire quickly and aren't reinstallable, while the file
# churns on every `brew upgrade` (noisy diffs, cross-machine conflicts). The
# Brewfiles are the source of truth (track-latest intent). See ~/.config/CLAUDE.md.
.config/brew/Brewfile*.lock.json
